a project in openshift is more like a kubernetes namespace... 

OpenShift Cluster
│
├── Projects
│     ├── Applications
│     ├── Deployments
│     ├── Services
│     ├── Routes
│     ├── ConfigMaps
│     └── Secrets
│
├── Cluster-wide Resources
│     ├── Nodes
│     ├── StorageClasses
│     ├── ClusterRoles
│     └── Operators
│
└── Infrastructure
      ├── Control Plane Nodes
      └── Worker Nodes

there's no more layer between cluster and project, but in enterprise it would commonly be built in this way:

Cluster
│
├── Finance Team
│     ├── finance-dev
│     ├── finance-test
│     └── finance-prod
│
└── Marketing Team
      ├── mkt-dev
      └── mkt-prod

in this case Finance Team and Marketing Team are not a layer, it would be set up through:
user groups
RBAC
naming conventions


